                    1.	PURPOSE &nbsp;  :
                </h2>
                <p style="margin-left:30px;">
                    The purpose of this procedure is to describe method for taking corrective action to eliminate
                    the cause of product / process / system non-conformities including customer complaints in
                    order to prevent recurrence.
                </p>

                <h2>
                    2.	SCOPE  &nbsp; :
                </h2>
                <p style="margin-left:30px;">Applicable to all non-conformities observed in product, process & system.  </p>
                <h2>3.	RESPONSIBILITY &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;:  </h2>

                <p style="margin-left:30px;">
                    Concerned department heads are responsible to implement & maintain this procedure.
                </p>

                <h2>

                    4.	PROCEDURE   &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;:
                </h2>
                <h5 style="margin-left:30px;">
                    Definition:
                </h5>

                <p style="margin-left:50px;">
                    Corrective Action means to eliminate the cause of nonconformities in order to prevent recurrence.
                </p>

                <h3 style="margin-left:30px;">
                    4.1  PRODUCT / PROCESS / SYSTEM NON-CONFORMITIES &nbsp;:
                </h3>
                <ol style="list-style:lower-alpha; margin-left:40px;">
                    <li>Whenever any product/process/system non-conformities observed, it is reported in corrective action report, form no. F MR 08. </li>
                    <li>Concerned department shall review the nature of non-conformity and identify the root cause. </li>
                    <li>Concerned department shall take necessary actions to correct the detected non-conformity. </li>
                    <li>Corrective action plan shall be decided based on the available facility with responsibility and target. </li>
                    <li>Responsible person shall implement the decided actions within the target and result of action taken shall be verified. </li>
                    <li>Effectiveness of action taken shall be reviewed. The details of non-conformity, root causes, corrective action plan, action taken and effectiveness shall be recorded in corrective action report, form no. F MR 08. </li>
                </ol>


